ATTACHMENT A
Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Blackstone Wind Farm II LLC Reactive Power Compensation May 25, 2018
BLACKSTONE WIND FARM II LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Blackstone Wind Farm II LLC ("Blackstone II") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Blackstone II generating facility ("Blackstone II Facility").
The Blackstone II Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Grundy County, Illinois. The Blackstone II Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Commonwealth Edison Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Blackstone II's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Blackstone II Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Blackstone II's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Blackstone II shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $720,000.00 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $60,000.00
